      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4> Different Exponential Representations</h4>\n<p>A table of values is shown below for a function \\(g(x)=(\\frac{1}{2})^x\\), which represents exponential decay.</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"89\">\n        <p align=\"center\">\\(x\\)</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"57\">\n        <p align=\"center\">&ndash;3</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"57\">\n        <p align=\"center\">&ndash;2</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"57\">\n        <p align=\"center\">&ndash;1</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"57\">\n        <p align=\"center\">0</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"64\">\n        <p align=\"center\">1</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"64\">\n        <p align=\"center\">2</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"64\">\n        <p align=\"center\">3</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"89\">\n        <p align=\"center\">\\(g(x) = (\\frac{1}{2})^x\\)</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"57\">\n        <p align=\"center\">8</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"57\">\n        <p align=\"center\">4</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"57\">\n        <p align=\"center\">2</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"57\">\n        <p align=\"center\">1</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"64\">\n        <p align=\"center\">\\(\\frac12\\)</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"64\">\n        <p align=\"center\">\\(\\frac14\\)</p>\n      </td>\n      <td valign=\"top\" width=\"64\">\n        <p align=\"center\">\\(\\frac18\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<br>\n<p>When these points are graphed, they show the decay because the function graphed decreases from left to right:</p>\n<p><img alt class=\"img-fluid atto_image_button_text-bottom\" height=\"568\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/640dc842516ed96046308a6b80d6a2df0ebdf749\" width=\"500\"></p>\n<h4> Try It: Different Exponential Representations</h4>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <p>Make a table for the function \\(f(x)=4^x\\). Then graph the function.</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p>Write down your answer, then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to check your work. </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal1\">\n  <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n  <p>Here is how to make a table and then graph the exponential function:</p>\n  <p>First, substitute values in for \\(x\\) to find the values of \\(f(x)\\).</p>\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n    <colgroup>\n      <col>\n      <col>\n      <col>\n      <col>\n      <col>\n      <col>\n    </colgroup>\n    <tbody>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <p>\\(x\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>0</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>1</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>2</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>3</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>4</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td>\n          <p> \\(f(x)=4^x\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>\\(4^0=1\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>\\(4^1=4\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>\\(4^2=16\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>\\(4^3=64\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td>\n          <p>\\(4^4=256\\)</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n  <br>\n  <p><img alt class=\"img-fluid atto_image_button_text-bottom\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/c4e972074be9c587e82641a2054c2fead8f5a718\" width=\"500\"></p>\n</div>"
